  Drop this block into the CLAUDE.md of any repo that uses Okareo. Claude
  reads CLAUDE.md at the start of every session, so it will know which
  plugin to ask for if the skills are missing. This is a soft contract —
  Claude cannot auto-install the plugin, but it will tell the person exactly
  what to run.
-->

## Okareo tooling

This project uses Okareo to simulate, evaluate, and monitor LLM and agent
behavior. The Okareo MCP server and skills ship as one Claude Code plugin.

One-time setup:

```
/plugin marketplace add okareo-ai/okareo-tools
/plugin install okareo@okareo
```

The plugin connects to the hosted Okareo MCP server; the first Okareo tool
call opens a browser for a one-time sign-in. No API key needs to be set for
the normal install — `OKAREO_API_KEY` is only required for headless/CI use.

The plugin provides four skills — `okareo-agent-simulation`,
`okareo-evaluation`, `okareo-monitoring`, and `okareo-scenario-from-traces`.
If an Okareo task runs and the relevant skill is not available, tell the
user to run the two commands above, then continue.
